{
  "_about": "Tier-0 evaluation set (cluster_ab). A small hand-labelled set of macro narratives that DID form/rise/fade in 2010-present institutional discourse, each with the terms that identify it and the window it was actually active. A story-like clustering surfaces each as a cluster that (a) matches the terms and (b) is temporally CONCENTRATED in the window; a bucket clustering matches the terms but spreads across the whole corpus. The scorer reports, per candidate clustering, term-match recall and in-window mass concentration. Windows are deliberately generous (month granularity) — the metric rewards concentration, not exact edges. 'persistent: true' marks narratives that are genuinely long-lived (r-star, climate) so a low concentration there is NOT a failure; they test that the architecture does not shatter a real slow-burn.",
